I wil briefly discover it to you;
                     Answ.
                   for I will give you but two Characters of it; many others might be had, but two I would bestow a little time to cleer to you. The one is,


                     Answ.
                  Then say I, Unquestionably, and without all dispute, it will appear faith hath its subordinate work, it is the declaration of the Lords mind in his Word, that faith meddles with, and all the Ordinances, and all tending upon the Word and Sacraments, &c. are the administrations of Christs will that is carried on in Ordinances, and no other way I know; sure I am the Scripture is silent in it: Therfore Friends (for such as are concerned in it, they wil not be here to hear it, nor any where


else, they count it a folly, but) to your sober Christians that desire to go to Heaven, and to walk with the Lord in his own way, give me leave to say this: Therefore,
